SIMPLE: compute
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Compute
<hw>Com*pute"</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocr⟧m*p⟦umac⟧t")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Computed</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Computing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>computare</ets>. See <er>Count</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety>
<def>To determine by calculation; to reckon; to count.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Two days, as we <qex>compute</qex> the days of heaven.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What's done we partly may <qex>compute</qex>,⟦br⟧
But know not what's resisted.</q> <rj><qau>Burns.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To calculate; number; count; reckon; estimate;
enumerate; rate. See <er>Calculate</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Compute</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Compute
<hw>Com*pute"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>computus</ets>: cf. F.
